    <abstract>
      <t>SRv6 as designed has evoked interest from various parties, though its deployment is being limited, amongst other things, by known security problems in its architecture. This document specifies a standard way to create a solution that closes some of the major security concerns, while retaining the tenants of the SRv6 protocol.</t>
